	(text_box "Theoretically, soldering R30 while leaving R78 and RV1 unsoldered is sufficient. However, if VBoost is not accurate enough, desolder R30 and solder R78 and RV1 instead. Adjusting RV1 should almost fully compensate for the internal voltage reference variation of the MT3608 and partially compensate for variations due to resistor network tolerance."
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 173.99 143.51 0)
		(size 102.87 20.32)
